editorialSummary.text: Chain providing office & packaging supplies, plus a variety of services such as shipping & printing.

originalText.text: This place is hell on earth and for paying 150% the regular print price I could get my printouts quicker after refilling their printer for them — rather than them printing. I came in here expecting nothing and wow. you’re welcome. I expect my check in the mail.

originalText.text:
I wish I could give zero stars because my experience was awful here. I went to the store twice in one day. The first time I went, I asked for labels to be made for a substantially sized shipment; the young man there was no help. I realized that labels could be made there (as that is a part of FedEx services), so I returned. Upon my second time, I tried to make my own labels, but realized there was no machine to do so. Due to this, I went back to the front desk.

There, I was met with April. When she saw the size of my order, it was apparent she did not want to help. Numerous times she stated she would have to type in the addresses herself. Trying to push us away and make our own, April attempted to make it clear she wasn't "rejecting us." So, I gave her a chance and started putting packages on the table. She then stopped us from putting packages on the table and reminded us she would have to type them individually. That is when I had enough. I took the packages and left. She also stated they were closing soon (at 7:00 PM), and I arrived at 4:50 PM. There was also no other customer there.

originalText.text: The worse experience ever! The sales lady acted as if I was such a trouble when asked for help with computer printing . She just can’t be bother, even rolled her eyes while answering my questions. I actually believe she was a racist, she said hello to all the other non Asian customers who walked in the door, meanwhile when I asked a simple question she couldn’t even bother to answer me. Save your money and go else where

originalText.text: My experience was laughably bad. Walked in needing to overnight some documents and include a return label-not anything complex. First I wait in line for 5 mins, which isn't a problem. Then at the front desk I'm told they can't do it there, and that I need to use a self service station. Odd, but ok. Then their self service station is giving me an error, so I go back to the desk, wait another 5 mins, and ask for help. They can't figure out the error, so they open up an new page on a different computer. I go through the steps, enter all my information, and then get an error because the printer is down. I go back and wait again for help, and a new person comes over and tells me that I can't print it, I have to email the label to myself, get on ANOTHER machine, log in, and print from my email to a different printer. At this point I'm tired of being given half assed instructions and begging for help from staff (who seem to be standing behind the desk, doing nothing, because they just direct everybody to the broken self serve stations). I took my documents, left, and walked to a ups and they handled my request in 5 minutes. I won't be using fedex again.

originalText.text: This was a standard FedEx location which isn’t saying a lot. No one really was helpful or all that friendly. But they did do what I needed done and the cost wasn’t too bad.  So I guess this is the best it is going to get for these stores. Someone should train their employees to focus on more friendly service.
